insights.text: Solid sample size: University of Portland 282 games vs BCIT Black 161. Trends are more trustworthy.

BCIT Black leads on win rate (53.5% vs 55.2%).
BCIT Black leads on k/d (1.06 vs 1.13).
University of Portland leads on dmg/r (144.41 vs 144.31).
BCIT Black leads on score/r (217.85 vs 218.98).
Biggest shared-map edge: University of Portland on Haven (win% gap 28.0 pts; samples 35g vs 25g).
Similar impact distribution (top-2 share: University of Portland ~45%, BCIT Black ~43%).
Both teams share key agent comfort picks: Viper.
